{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775856836887,"sessionID":"ses_286af4893ffeX2sOYYYMeuxzmQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7950e113001A8v4iL6SjJ95XT","messageID":"msg_d7950d900001P3W65KSGT7WH2v","sessionID":"ses_286af4893ffeX2sOYYYMeuxzmQ","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775856840597,"sessionID":"ses_286af4893ffeX2sOYYYMeuxzmQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7950e3d0001sYkiDLjcRrGmpc","messageID":"msg_d7950d900001P3W65KSGT7WH2v","sessionID":"ses_286af4893ffeX2sOYYYMeuxzmQ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_b0e3bca4a3314801a931a135","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-016 тАФ PicoD цЦЗф╗╢чобчРЖ API\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement file management REST API for the PicoD service in `pkg/picod`, enabling upload, download, list, and deletion of files within sandbox workspaces. The API integrates with the existing Kubernetes client-go library for resource management.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: The PicoD service (AR-015) runs as a sandbox execution environment requiring file management capabilities for code execution workflows. Current implementation includes basic file handlers but needs a structured REST API surface with proper error handling, path validation, and integration with the agentcube client-go library.\n12: \n13: ### Goal\n14: \n15: Implement a comprehensive file management REST API in `pkg/picod` with:\n16: - RESTful endpoints for file CRUD operations\n17: - Path sanitization and security validation\n18: - Support for multipart and JSON-base64 upload formats\n19: - Integration with client-go for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter resource management\n20: \n21: ### Value\n22: - Complete file management capabilities for sandbox environments\n23: - Standardized REST API matching Kubernetes conventions\n24: - Path security to prevent directory traversal attacks\n25: - Support for both direct file upload and base64-encoded content\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## Scope\n30: \n31: ### In-Scope\n32: \n33: | Deliverable | Description |\n34: |-------------|-------------|\n35: | File upload endpoint | POST /api/v1/files тАФ multipart and JSON-base64 |\n36: | File download endpoint | GET /api/v1/files/*path |\n37: | File list endpoint | GET /api/v1/files?path=... |\n38: | File delete endpoint | DELETE /api/v1/files/*path |\n39: | Path sanitization | Validate and constrain paths to workspace directory |\n40: | Client-go integration | Resource read/write via informers/listers |\n41: \n42: ### API Endpoints\n43: \n44: | Method | Path | Description |\n45: |--------|------|-------------|\n46: | POST | /api/v1/files | Upload file (multipart or JSON-base64) |\n47: | GET | /api/v1/files | List files in directory |\n48: | GET | /api/v1/files/*path | Download file |\n49: | DELETE | /api/v1/files/*path | Delete file or directory |\n50: \n51: ### Data Types\n52: \n53: ```go\n54: type FileInfo struct {\n55:     Path     string    `json:\"path\"`\n56:     Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n57:     Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n58:     Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n59: }\n60: \n61: type UploadFileRequest struct {\n62:     Path    string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n63:     Content string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"`\n64:     Mode    string `json:\"mode\"`\n65: }\n66: \n67: type FileEntry struct {\n68:     Name     string    `json:\"name\"`\n69:     Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n70:     Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n71:     Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n72:     IsDir    bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`\n73: }\n74: \n75: type ListFilesResponse struct {\n76:     Files []FileEntry `json:\"files\"`\n77: }\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ### Code Structure\n81: \n82: ```\n83: pkg/picod/\n84: тФЬтФАтФА files.go           # File handlers (upload, download, list, delete)\n85: тФЬтФАтФА server.go          # Server struct and initialization\n86: тФЬтФАтФА config.go          # Configuration parsing\n87: тФЬтФАтФА auth.go            # Authentication middleware\n88: тФЬтФАтФА execute.go         # Code execution handlers\n89: тФЬтФАтФА health.go          # Health check endpoints\n90: тФЬтФАтФА picod_test.go      # Unit tests\n91: тФФтФАтФА main.go            # Entry point\n92: ```\n93: \n94: ### Configuration\n95: \n96: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n97: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n98: | PICOD_PORT | No | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n99: | PICOD_WORKSPACE_DIR | Yes | - | Base workspace directory |\n100: | PICOD_AUTH_TOKEN | No | - | Authentication token |\n101: | KUBERNETES_MODE | No | false | Enable Kubernetes client-go |\n102: | KUBERNETES_API_SERVER | No | in-cluster | API server URL |\n103: | KUBERNETES_CONFIG | No | in-cluster | kubeconfig path |\n104: \n105: ### Out-of-Scope\n106: - File streaming for large files (>100MB)\n107: - Directory creation endpoint (implicit via upload)\n108: - File move/rename operations\n109: - File content search\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## Impact Analysis\n114: \n115: ### Dependencies\n116: \n117: | Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n118: |------------|--------|---------|\n119: | github.com/gin-gonic/gin | ^1.x | HTTP framework |\n120: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client | local | Kubernetes client-go |\n121: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1 | local | CRD types |\n122: | k8s.io/klog/v2 | ^2.x | Logging |\n123: | k8s.io/client-go | ^0.34.x | Kubernetes client |\n124: \n125: ### Upstream\n126: \n127: - **AR-015 PicoD Service** тАФ Base service infrastructure\n128: - **client-go library** тАФ Generated Kubernetes client (deployment/client-go.md)\n129: - **pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1** тАФ AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types\n130: \n131: ### Downstream Consumers\n132: \n133: 1. **Code Execution Workflows** тАФ Source file upload, output retrieval\n134: 2. **IDE Integrations** тАФ File sync capabilities\n135: 3. **Test Frameworks** тАФ Test file deployment\n136: \n137: ### Risks\n138: \n139: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n140: |------|----------|------------|\n141: | Path traversal | High | SanitizePath with workspace root validation |\n142: | Large file DoS | Medium | Size limits on upload |\n143: | Path injection | Medium | Reject absolute paths and parent directory refs |\n144: | Concurrent writes | Low | OS-level file locking for overwrite detection |\n145: \n146: ---\n147: \n148: ## Alternatives Considered\n149: \n150: ### Option 1: Direct Filesystem Access (Selected)\n151: \n152: **Approach**: Use Go's os/std library directly for file operations.\n153: \n154: **Pros**:\n155: - Simple implementation\n156: - No external dependencies\n157: - Direct control over file operations\n158: - Works in any environment\n159: \n160: **Cons**:\n161: - No distributed filesystem support\n162: - Local-only storage\n163: \n164: **Decision**: Selected тАФ aligns with PicoD's isolated sandbox model.\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ### Option 2: Kubernetes PersistentVolume\n169: \n170: **Approach**: Mount PVC for workspace storage.\n171: \n172: **Pros**:\n173: - Persistent across pod restarts\n174: - Distributed access\n175: \n176: **Cons**:\n177: - Requires PVC provisioning\n178: - Overhead for ephemeral sandboxes\n179: - Complex lifecycle management\n180: \n181: **Decision**: Deferred тАФ not needed for ephemeral execution model.\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ### Option 3: Object Storage (S3/MinIO)\n186: \n187: **Approach**: Store files in object storage.\n188: \n189: **Pros**:\n190: - Scalable\n191: - Built-in redundancy\n192: \n193: **Cons**:\n194: - Network latency\n195: - Additional infrastructure\n196: - Not needed for execution artifacts\n197: \n198: **Decision**: Deferred тАФ future consideration for multi-pod deployments.\n199: \n200: ---\n201: \n202: ## Implementation Plan\n203: \n204: ### Phase 1: Core Handlers\n205: - [x] UploadFileHandler тАФ multipart and JSON-base64\n206: - [x] ListFilesHandler тАФ directory listing\n207: - [x] DownloadFileHandler тАФ file retrieval\n208: - [ ] DeleteFileHandler тАФ file/directory removal\n209: - [x] Path sanitization with workspace root validation\n210: \n211: ### Phase 2: Client-go Integration\n212: - [ ] Initialize SharedInformerFactory\n213: - [ ] Wire AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter listers\n214: - [ ] Add resource watch handlers\n215: \n216: ### Phase 3: Error Handling\n217: - [ ] Consistent error response format\n218: - [ ] Status code standardization\n219: - [ ] Logging integration\n220: \n221: ### Phase 4: Testing\n222: - [ ] Unit tests for each handler\n223: - [ ] Path sanitization edge cases\n224: - [ ] Integration tests with client-go\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ## Acceptance Criteria\n229: \n230: - [x] POST /api/v1/files accepts multipart/form-data\n231: - [x] POST /api/v1/files accepts application/json with base64 content\n232: - [x] GET /api/v1/files lists directory contents\n233: - [x] GET /api/v1/files/*path downloads file\n234: - [x] DELETE /api/v1/files/*path removes file/directory\n235: - [x] Path traversal attacks prevented via SanitizePath\n236: - [x] Absolute paths rejected\n237: - [x] Parent directory references (..) rejected\n238: - [x] Files constrained to workspace directory\n239: - [x] File mode parsed from request (octal string)\n240: - [x] Default file mode 0644\n241: - [x] ListFilesResponse returns proper FileEntry array\n242: - [x] 404 returned for non-existent paths\n243: - [x] 400 returned for invalid requests\n244: - [ ] Client-go informer factory initialized\n245: - [ ] AgentRuntime lister integrated\n\n(End of file - total 245 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-016 тАФ PicoD цЦЗф╗╢чобчРЖ API\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement file management REST API for the PicoD service in `pkg/picod`, enabling upload, download, list, and deletion of files within sandbox workspaces. The API integrates with the existing Kubernetes client-go library for resource management.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe PicoD service (AR-015) runs as a sandbox execution environment requiring file management capabilities for code execution workflows. Current implementation includes basic file handlers but needs a structured REST API surface with proper error handling, path validation, and integration with the agentcube client-go library.\n\n### Goal\n\nImplement a comprehensive file management REST API in `pkg/picod` with:\n- RESTful endpoints for file CRUD operations\n- Path sanitization and security validation\n- Support for multipart and JSON-base64 upload formats\n- Integration with client-go for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter resource management\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775856840579,"end":1775856840595}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775856840601,"sessionID":"ses_286af4893ffeX2sOYYYMeuxzmQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7950e749001u2a1VjP3inJKrc","messageID":"msg_d7950d900001P3W65KSGT7WH2v","sessionID":"ses_286af4893ffeX2sOYYYMeuxzmQ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_50d1f6bd9d0f440eae0079dc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/picod/auth.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/picod/auth.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package picod\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"crypto/rsa\"\n5: \t\"crypto/x509\"\n6: \t\"encoding/pem\"\n7: \t\"errors\"\n8: \t\"fmt\"\n9: \t\"net/http\"\n10: \t\"os\"\n11: \t\"strings\"\n12: \t\"sync\"\n13: \t\"time\"\n14: \n15: \t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n16: \t\"github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5\"\n17: \t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n18: )\n19: \n20: const (\n21: \tPublicKeyEnvVar = \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"\n22: \tMaxBodySize     = 32 << 20\n23: )\n24: \n25: type AuthManager struct {\n26: \tpublicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n27: \tmutex     sync.RWMutex\n28: }\n29: \n30: func NewAuthManager() *AuthManager {\n31: \treturn &AuthManager{}\n32: }\n33: \n34: func (am *AuthManager) LoadPublicKeyFromEnv() error {\n35: \tkeyData := os.Getenv(PublicKeyEnvVar)\n36: \tif keyData == \"\" {\n37: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"environment variable %s is not set\", PublicKeyEnvVar)\n38: \t}\n39: \n40: \tblock, _ := pem.Decode([]byte(keyData))\n41: \tif block == nil {\n42: \t\treturn errors.New(\"failed to decode PEM block\")\n43: \t}\n44: \n45: \tpubKey, err := x509.ParsePKIXPublicKey(block.Bytes)\n46: \tif err != nil {\n47: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse public key: %w\", err)\n48: \t}\n49: \n50: \trsaPubKey, ok := pubKey.(*rsa.PublicKey)\n51: \tif !ok {\n52: \t\treturn errors.New(\"public key is not an RSA key\")\n53: \t}\n54: \n55: \tam.mutex.Lock()\n56: \tam.publicKey = rsaPubKey\n57: \tam.mutex.Unlock()\n58: \n59: \treturn nil\n60: }\n61: \n62: func (am *AuthManager) GetPublicKey() *rsa.PublicKey {\n63: \tam.mutex.RLock()\n64: \tdefer am.mutex.RUnlock()\n65: \treturn am.publicKey\n66: }\n67: \n68: func (am *AuthManager) AuthMiddleware() gin.HandlerFunc {\n69: \treturn func(c *gin.Context) {\n70: \t\tauthHeader := c.GetHeader(\"Authorization\")\n71: \t\tif authHeader == \"\" {\n72: \t\t\tc.AbortWithStatusJSON(401, gin.H{\n73: \t\t\t\t\"error\":  \"Missing authorization header\",\n74: \t\t\t\t\"code\":   401,\n75: \t\t\t\t\"detail\": \"JWT required: Use Bearer <token>\",\n76: \t\t\t})\n77: \t\t\treturn\n78: \t\t}\n79: \n80: \t\tparts := strings.Split(authHeader, \" \")\n81: \t\tif len(parts) != 2 || parts[0] != \"Bearer\" {\n82: \t\t\tc.AbortWithStatusJSON(401, gin.H{\n83: \t\t\t\t\"error\":  \"Invalid authorization header format\",\n84: \t\t\t\t\"code\":   401,\n85: \t\t\t\t\"detail\": \"Use Bearer <token>\",\n86: \t\t\t})\n87: \t\t\treturn\n88: \t\t}\n89: \n90: \t\ttokenString := parts[1]\n91: \n92: \t\tam.mutex.RLock()\n93: \t\tpubKey := am.publicKey\n94: \t\tam.mutex.RUnlock()\n95: \n96: \t\tif pubKey == nil {\n97: \t\t\tc.AbortWithStatusJSON(401, gin.H{\n98: \t\t\t\t\"error\":  \"Invalid token\",\n99: \t\t\t\t\"code\":   401,\n100: \t\t\t\t\"detail\": \"Public key not configured\",\n101: \t\t\t})\n102: \t\t\treturn\n103: \t\t}\n104: \n105: \t\ttoken, err := jwt.Parse(tokenString, func(token *jwt.Token) (interface{}, error) {\n106: \t\t\tif _, ok := token.Method.(*jwt.SigningMethodRSA); !ok {\n107: \t\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected signing method: %v\", token.Header[\"alg\"])\n108: \t\t\t}\n109: \t\t\treturn pubKey, nil\n110: \t\t}, jwt.WithExpirationRequired(), jwt.WithIssuedAt(), jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute))\n111: \n112: \t\tif err != nil || !token.Valid {\n113: \t\t\tdetail := \"verification failed\"\n114: \t\t\tif err != nil {\n115: \t\t\t\tdetail = err.Error()\n116: \t\t\t}\n117: \t\t\tc.AbortWithStatusJSON(401, gin.H{\n118: \t\t\t\t\"error\":  \"Invalid token\",\n119: \t\t\t\t\"code\":   401,\n120: \t\t\t\t\"detail\": detail,\n121: \t\t\t})\n122: \t\t\treturn\n123: \t\t}\n124: \n125: \t\tc.Request.Body = http.MaxBytesReader(c.Writer, c.Request.Body, MaxBodySize)\n126: \t\tc.Next()\n127: \t}\n128: }\n129: \n130: func (am *AuthManager) RequireAuth() gin.HandlerFunc {\n131: \treturn func(c *gin.Context) {\n132: \t\tif err := am.LoadPublicKeyFromEnv(); err != nil {\n133: \t\t\tklog.Fatalf(\"Failed to load public key: %v\", err)\n134: \t\t}\n135: \t\tam.AuthMiddleware()(c)\n136: \t}\n137: }\n\n(End of file - total 137 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package picod\n\nimport (\n\t\"crypto/rsa\"\n\t\"crypto/x509\"\n\t\"encoding/pem\"\n\t\"errors\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"net/http\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\t\"sync\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n\t\"github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5\"\n\t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n)\n\nconst (","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/picod/auth.go","time":{"start":1775856840583,"end":1775856840599}}}}
