{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775856889190,"sessionID":"ses_286af4893ffeX2sOYYYMeuxzmQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7951543c001Kw0haaQ2hdbU3I","messageID":"msg_d795120e4001f4ZbMzEQrBiqeE","sessionID":"ses_286af4893ffeX2sOYYYMeuxzmQ","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_6fb03a4fb09a4003acba10f4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: AR-017 тАФ PicoD JWT ф╕нщЧ┤ф╗╢хвЮх╝║\n\n## Summary\n\nEnhance the existing JWT authentication middleware in `pkg/picod` with configurable public paths, dynamic public key rotation, and flexible token extraction. The enhancement improves the current auth.go implementation to better support production deployment scenarios.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe current PicoD service (AR-015) includes basic JWT authentication via `AuthManager` in `pkg/picod/auth.go`. The implementation loads an RSA public key from the `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable and validates Bearer tokens on all `/api/*` endpoints. However, the current implementation lacks:\n\n- Public path configuration (endpoints that don't require authentication)\n- Dynamic public key rotation without service restart\n- Support for token extraction via query parameters\n- Granular error handling matching the router package patterns\n\n### Goal\n\nEnhance the PicoD JWT middleware in `pkg/picod` with:\n- Configurable public paths via environment variable\n- Dynamic public key hot-reload via SIGHUP signal\n- Optional query parameter token support\n- Consistent error response format with error codes\n\n### Value\n- Production-ready authentication with flexible configuration\n- Zero-downtime public key rotation for security operations\n- Support for API clients that prefer query parameter token passing\n- Consistency with the router package error handling patterns\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| Public path configuration | Environment variable `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_PATHS` for exempt endpoints |\n| Dynamic key reload | SIGHUP signal handler to reload public key without restart |\n| Query parameter support | Environment variable `PICOD_AUTH_ALLOW_QUERY_PARAM` to enable token in URL |\n| Error response standardization | Consistent `error_code` field in error responses |\n| Configuration struct | AuthConfig for middleware options |\n\n### Configuration\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY | Yes | - | PEM-encoded RSA public key |\n| PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_PATHS | No | /health | Comma-separated paths that skip auth |\n| PICOD_AUTH_ALLOW_QUERY_PARAM | No | false | Enable token via ?token= query param |\n| PICOD_JWT_ISSUER | No | - | Expected JWT issuer claim |\n| PICOD_JWT_AUDIENCE | No | - | Expected JWT audience claim |\n\n### Code Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/\nтФЬтФАтФА auth.go           # Existing AuthManager (to be enhanced)\nтФЬтФАтФА auth_config.go   # NEW: AuthConfig struct and loading\nтФЬтФАтФА auth_middleware.go  # NEW: Enhanced middleware with options\nтФЬтФАтФА server.go        # Updated: Use new middleware with config\nтФФтФАтФА main.go          # No changes needed\n```\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n- Token refresh/reissue endpoints\n- Rate limiting on auth failures\n- Login endpoint implementation\n- Multi-tenant namespace isolation\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n|------------|--------|---------|\n| github.com/gin-gonic/gin | existing | HTTP framework |\n| github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 | existing | JWT validation |\n| k8s.io/klog/v2 | existing | Logging |\n| os/signal (stdlib) | existing | SIGHUP handling |\n\n### Upstream\n\n- **AR-015 PicoD Service** тАФ Existing authentication foundation\n- **pkg/router/jwt_middleware.go** тАФ Reference implementation patterns\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **Code Execution Clients** тАФ Must provide valid JWT in Authorization header\n2. **File Management Clients** тАФ Same auth requirements\n3. **Monitoring Systems** тАФ May use /health without auth\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Key rotation race condition | Medium | RWMutex for key access during reload |\n| Query param token leakage | Medium | Disable by default, warn in docs |\n| Invalid public key reload | Low | Validate new key before replacing, rollback on failure |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: Current Implementation (Baseline)\n\n**Approach**: Keep existing auth.go as-is without enhancements.\n\n**Pros**:\n- No code changes required\n- Stable and tested\n- Simpler to maintain\n\n**Cons**:\n- No public path flexibility\n- Requires service restart for key rotation\n- No query param support\n\n**Decision**: Not selected тАФ insufficient for production operations.\n\n---\n\n### Option 2: Full Integration with Router Package (Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Create auth_config.go and auth_middleware.go in pkg/picod, using patterns from pkg/router/jwt_middleware.go.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Consistent error handling with router package\n- Public path configuration support\n- Dynamic key rotation\n- Query parameter support option\n\n**Cons**:\n- Additional code to maintain\n- Slight increase in complexity\n\n**Decision**: Selected тАФ balances flexibility with maintainability.\n\n---\n\n### Option 3: Use External Auth Service\n\n**Approach**: Delegate authentication to an external service (e.g., OAuth2 proxy).\n\n**Pros**:\n- Offloads auth complexity\n- Standard auth flows (OAuth2, OIDC)\n- Centralized key management\n\n**Cons**:\n- Additional infrastructure dependency\n- Network latency for auth checks\n- Not aligned with current architecture\n\n**Decision**: Deferred тАФ future consideration if multi-tenant requirements emerge.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Configuration Support\n- [ ] Create auth_config.go with AuthConfig struct\n- [ ] Add environment variable parsing for new config options\n- [ ] Add validation for issuer/audience claims\n\n### Phase 2: Enhanced Middleware\n- [ ] Create auth_middleware.go with enhanced MiddlewareFunc\n- [ ] Implement public path checking\n- [ ] Implement query parameter token extraction\n- [ ] Add issuer/audience claim validation\n\n### Phase 3: Dynamic Key Rotation\n- [ ] Add SIGHUP signal handler in server.go\n- [ ] Implement hot-reload of public key\n- [ ] Add validation before replacing key\n\n### Phase 4: Integration\n- [ ] Update server.go to use enhanced middleware\n- [ ] Update error response format for consistency\n\n### Phase 5: Testing\n- [ ] Unit tests for public path configuration\n- [ ] Unit tests for key hot-reload\n- [ ] Unit tests for query parameter extraction\n- [ ] Integration tests with mock JWT tokens\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Public paths configurable via PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_PATHS\n- [ ] SIGHUP signal triggers public key reload\n- [ ] Query parameter token extraction works when enabled\n- [ ] Issuer and audience claims validated when configured\n- [ ] Error responses include error_code field\n- [ ] Key rotation is atomic (no race conditions)\n- [ ] Default public path /health works without auth\n- [ ] All existing functionality preserved (backward compatible)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/store/store_valkey.go\">\nERROR [157:44] vs.cli.B().Zadd().Key(vs.expiryIndexKey).ZaddScoreMember undefined (type cmds.ZaddKey has no field or method ZaddScoreMember)\nERROR [157:67] undefined: valkey.ZaddScoreMember\nERROR [158:50] vs.cli.B().Zadd().Key(vs.lastActivityIndexKey).ZaddScoreMember undefined (type cmds.ZaddKey has no field or method ZaddScoreMember)\nERROR [158:73] undefined: valkey.ZaddScoreMember\nER